        });

      const isAvailable = () => {
        if (isLocalStorageAvailable) {
          return true;
        }
  
        try {
          const x = "__storage_test__";
          window.localStorage.setItem(x, x);
          window.localStorage.removeItem(x);
          isLocalStorageAvailable = true;

        } catch (e) {
          return false;
        }
      };
  
      const unsafeSetItem = (key, value) => {
        window.localStorage.setItem(key, JSON.stringify(value));
      };
  
      const unsafeGetItem = (key) => {
        return JSON.parse(window.localStorage.getItem(key) || "null");
      };
  
      const setSafeItem = (key, value) => {
        if (isAvailable()) {
          unsafeSetItem(key, value);
        }
      };

        return isAvailable() ? unsafeGetItem(key) : defaultValue;
      };

  <script>
  function initialize_wunderkind(d) {
    window.addEventListener('load', function() {
      var e = d.createElement('script');
      e.src = d.location.protocol + '//tag.wknd.ai/5453/i.js';
      e.async = true;
      d.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(e);
    });
  }

  function determine_wunderkind_eligibility() {
    if (window.location.search.includes('enable_wunderkind')) {
      initialize_wunderkind(document);
      return;
    }

    let wunderkind_segment = 0;
    try { wunderkind_segment = localStorage.getItem('genius_wunderkind_segment'); } catch (e) {}

    if (typeof(wunderkind_segment) === 'string') {
      wunderkind_segment = Number(wunderkind_segment);
    } else {
      wunderkind_segment = Math.random();
      try { localStorage.setItem('genius_wunderkind_segment', wunderkind_segment); } catch (e) {}
    }

    if ((wunderkind_segment * 100) < 100.0) {
      window['com.Genius.wunderkind_cohort'] = 'wunderkind';
      initialize_wunderkind(document);
    } else {
      window['com.Genius.wunderkind_cohort'] = 'control';
    }
  }

  determine_wunderkind_eligibility();
</script>

<p>The song re-entered the Billboard Hot 100,  as well as public consciousness, yet again with the release of the <a href="http://imdb.com/title/tt1727824/" rel="noopener nofollow"><i>Bohemian Rhapsody</i> biopic</a> in November of 2018. <p>The word <a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/bohemian-artistic-subculture" rel="noopener nofollow">â€œBohemianâ€</a> seems to refer to a group of artists and musicians from the 19th century, known for defying convention and living with disregard for standards; as opposed to the region of <a href="https://www.britannica.com/place/Bohemia" rel="noopener nofollow">Bohemia</a> in the Czech Republic. <p>Mercury let these lyrics â€œbeâ€ open to interpretation.  The song was a seedling as â€œThe Cowboy Songâ€. <p>Mary Austin was Freddieâ€™s dearest friend and family-member, by default and design. <p>Queenâ€™s monetary health (especially Freddieâ€™s) began with the success of Bo-Rap and their fourth album, â€œA Night at the Operaâ€. <p>So was Freddie Mercury â€œgayâ€?  Or was he â€œbi-sexualâ€?  Is â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ his obvious â€œcoming outâ€ song? It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with \\\"These Are the Days of Our Lives\\\" two weeks after Freddie Mercury\'s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie *[Wayne\'s World](http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/)*. In 2002, the song was listed at #1 in [a Guinness World Records poll](http://www.queenarchives.com/index.php?title=Brian_May_-_08-XX-2002_-_Burns_Guitar_-_Canadian_Musician) as Britain\'s favourite single of all time---ranking higher than four [Beatles](https://genius.com/artists/The-beatles) tracks and [\\\"Imagine\\\"](https://genius.com/John-lennon-imagine-lyrics) by [John Lennon](https://genius.com/artists/John-lennon). In 2004, the song was inducted into the Grammy Hall of Fame. \\n\\nThe song re-entered the Billboard Hot 100,  as well as public consciousness, yet again with the release of the [<i>Bohemian Rhapsody<\/i> biopic](imdb.com/title/tt1727824/) in November of 2018. The movie grossed about \$910.8 million worldwide, and made the song \\\"the [most streamed song](https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/11/entertainment/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-streams/index.html) of the 20th century\\\" with over 1.6 billion downloads across all major streaming services. And on March 25, 2021, The Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) certified Queen\'s \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" diamond. \\n\\nComplex and operatic both musically and lyrically, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" (like [Led Zeppelin](/artists/Led-zeppelin)\'s [\\\"Stairway to Heaven\\\"](/Led-zeppelin-stairway-to-heaven-lyrics) and [The Eagles](/artists/The-eagles)\' [\\\"Hotel California\\\"](/The-eagles-hotel-california-lyrics)) has attracted endless fan theories and commentary. â€”@Genius\",\"state\":\"accepted\",\"source\":null,\"shareUrl\":\"https://genius.com/3490803\",\"referentId\":3490803,\"pyongsCount\":5,\"proposedEditCount\":1,\"pinned\":false,\"needsExegesis\":false,\"id\":3490803,\"hasVoters\":true,\"embedContent\":\"<blockquote class=\'rg_standalone_container\' data-src=\'//genius.com/annotations/3490803/standalone_embed\'><a href=\'https://genius.com/3490803/Queen-bohemian-rhapsody/Bohemian-rhapsody\'>Bohemian Rhapsody<\/a><br><a href=\'https://genius.com/Queen-bohemian-rhapsody-lyrics\'>&#8213; Queen â€“ Bohemian Rhapsody<\/a><\/blockquote><script async crossorigin src=\'//genius.com/annotations/load_standalone_embeds.js\'><\/script>\",\"deleted\":false,\"customPreview\":null,\"createdAt\":1296083543,\"community\":true,\"commentCount\":0,\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"Widely considered to be one of the [greatest songs of all time](http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/the-500-greatest-songs-of-all-time-20110407/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-20110526), \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" was the first single released from Queen\'s fourth studio album, *[A Night at the Opera](http://genius.com/albums/Queen/A-night-at-the-opera)*. It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with \\\"These Are the Days of Our Lives\\\" two weeks after Freddie Mercury\'s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie *[Wayne\'s World](http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/)*. In 2002, the song was listed at #1 in [a Guinness World Records poll](http://www.queenarchives.com/index.php?title=Brian_May_-_08-XX-2002_-_Burns_Guitar_-_Canadian_Musician) as Britain\'s favourite single of all time---ranking higher than four [Beatles](https://genius.com/artists/The-beatles) tracks and [\\\"Imagine\\\"](https://genius.com/John-lennon-imagine-lyrics) by [John Lennon](https://genius.com/artists/John-lennon). In 2004, the song was inducted into the Grammy Hall of Fame. \\n\\nThe song re-entered the Billboard Hot 100,  as well as public consciousness, yet again with the release of the [<i>Bohemian Rhapsody<\/i> biopic](imdb.com/title/tt1727824/) in November of 2018. The movie grossed about \$910.8 million worldwide, and made the song \\\"the [most streamed song](https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/11/entertainment/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-streams/index.html) of the 20th century\\\" with over 1.6 billion downloads across all major streaming services. And on March 25, 2021, The Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) certified Queen\'s \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" diamond. \\n\\nComplex and operatic both musically and lyrically, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" (like [Led Zeppelin](/artists/Led-zeppelin)\'s [\\\"Stairway to Heaven\\\"](/Led-zeppelin-stairway-to-heaven-lyrics) and [The Eagles](/artists/The-eagles)\' [\\\"Hotel California\\\"](/The-eagles-hotel-california-lyrics)) has attracted endless fan theories and commentary. The surviving band members have [claimed](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3593532.stm) that the narrative is based on the [Faust legend](http://genius.com/albums/Johann-wolfgang-von-goethe/Faust-english); critics have found possible sources in opera and Freddie Mercury\'s personal biography; but like any good piece of art, it\'s open to interpretation.\\n\\nThe word [\\\"Bohemian\\\"](https://www.britannica.com/topic/bohemian-artistic-subculture) seems to refer to a group of artists and musicians from the 19th century, known for defying convention and living with disregard for standards; as opposed to the region of [Bohemia](https://www.britannica.com/place/Bohemia) in the Czech Republic. Meanwhile the term [\\\"rhapsody\\\"](https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/rhapsody) (derived from the Greek: á¿¥Î±Ïˆá¿³Î´ÏŒÏ‚ or rhapsÅidos for a reciter of epic poetry, or a rhapsodist) is a piece of classical music with distinct sections that are played as one movement. Rhapsodies often feature dense themes or narratives.\\n\\n\\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" has got a very diverse song structure. It includes:\\nâ€¢\\t**Intro** (0:00-0:49) \\nâ€¢\\t**Ballad section** (0:49-2:37)\\nâ€¢\\t**Brian Mayâ€˜s guitar solo** (2:37-3:05)\\nâ€¢\\t**Operatic verse** (3:05-4:07)\\nâ€¢\\t**Hard-rock verse** (4:07-4:54)\\nâ€¢\\t**Coda** (4:54-5:55)\",\"html\":\"<p>Widely considered to be one of the <a href=\\\"http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/the-500-greatest-songs-of-all-time-20110407/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-20110526\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">greatest songs of all time<\/a>, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ was the first single released from Queenâ€™s fourth studio album, <em><a href=\\\"https://genius.com/albums/Queen/A-night-at-the-opera\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/albums/35169\\\">A Night at the Opera<\/a><\/em>. It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with â€œThese Are the Days of Our Livesâ€ two weeks after Freddie Mercuryâ€™s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie <em><a href=\\\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">Wayneâ€™s World<\/a><\/em>. In 2004, the song was inducted into the Grammy Hall of Fame.<\/p>\\n\\n<p>The song re-entered the Billboard Hot 100,  as well as public consciousness, yet again with the release of the <a href=\\\"http://imdb.com/title/tt1727824/\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\"><i>Bohemian Rhapsody<\/i> biopic<\/a> in November of 2018. The movie grossed about \$910.8 million worldwide, and made the song â€œthe <a href=\\\"https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/11/entertainment/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-streams/index.html\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">most streamed song<\/a> of the 20th centuryâ€ with over 1.6 billion downloads across all major streaming services. And on March 25, 2021, The Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) certified Queenâ€™s â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ diamond.<\/p>\\n\\n<p>Complex and operatic both musically and lyrically, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ (like <a href=\\\"https://genius.com/artists/Led-zeppelin\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/artists/562\\\">Led Zeppelin<\/a>â€™s <a href=\\\"https://genius.com/Led-zeppelin-stairway-to-heaven-lyrics\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/songs/1061\\\">â€œStairway to Heavenâ€<\/a> and <a href=\\\"https://genius.com/artists/The-eagles\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/artists/561\\\">The Eagles<\/a>â€˜ <a href=\\\"https://genius.com/The-eagles-hotel-california-lyrics\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/songs/1060\\\">â€œHotel Californiaâ€<\/a>) has attracted endless fan theories and commentary. The surviving band members have <a href=\\\"http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3593532.stm\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">claimed<\/a> that the narrative is based on the <a href=\\\"https://genius.com/albums/Johann-wolfgang-von-goethe/Faust-english\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\" data-api_path=\\\"/albums/50019\\\">Faust legend<\/a>; critics have found possible sources in opera and Freddie Mercuryâ€™s personal biography; but like any good piece of art, itâ€™s open to interpretation.<\/p>\\n\\n<p>The word <a href=\\\"https://www.britannica.com/topic/bohemian-artistic-subculture\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">â€œBohemianâ€<\/a> seems to refer to a group of artists and musicians from the 19th century, known for defying convention and living with disregard for standards; as opposed to the region of <a href=\\\"https://www.britannica.com/place/Bohemia\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">Bohemia<\/a> in the Czech Republic. It became associated with that sort of lifestyle because <a href=\\\"http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=bohemian\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">the French thought that was where travelling Romani communities came from.<\/a><\/p>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"110739\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":4365014,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.998780487804878,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":7447663,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.0012195121951219512,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":71,\"id\":110739,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1525197790,\"bodyForEdit\":\"\\\"Objection, your Honor: context!\\\" Re-phrase:\\n\\nIn late 1975, when Bo Rap\'s thunderbolts and lightning cast Queen as rock-gods, was Mercury struck as very, very **openly** gay?  \\n\\nTo \\\"be gay\\\", or \\\"not to be gay\\\", in mid-1970\'s England, was that a question of psychiatric, legal, and/or religious ramifications?  Mamma mia; \\\"Spare him his life from\\\" such monstrosities\\\", right? \\n\\nBo-Rap is a thrill ride shape-shifter, from tragic tear-jerk-trigger-pulling proportions to the comedically scary mock-opera trial parts.  It took \\\"Wayne\'s World\\\" to push on the gas of the thrill ride back up the U.S. charts to not-quite-#1.  Before the snooty over-analysis to follow, let\'s get one thing straight: this song has plenty of Bohemian comedy, so line up your opera spectacles (is \\\"opera\\\" gay?).   And let\'s not forget the B-side: Roger\'s \\\"[I\'m in Love With My Car](/Queen-im-in-love-with-my-car-lyrics)\\\".  Was he, then, motorosexual?  Metrosexual?  It\'s all dripping in the metaphorical.  Words, words, words, must be carefully chosen: ask [Oscar Wilde](/artists/Oscar-wilde) or anyone accused of being heretical by the Papacy (scarier than reigning Queens, like certain ... nevermind).\\n\\nWas Galileo imprisoned for his heliocentrism?  Galileo Galilei was a [*Sheer Heretic*](https://genius.com/albums/Queen/Sheer-heart-attack/), no? And if Dr. Brian May played the role of the 17th Century Astronomer, then who is Figaro, and were THEY straight?  Was the earth flat?  \\\"Objection, your Honor!\\\" \\n\\nSustained; irreverent.  Scaramouche, re-direct the \\\"gay connotations\\\" rotation annotation to the 20th to 21st century.  Proceed:\\n\\nMany folks interpret Bo Rap\'s lyrics as Mercury\'s metaphoric struggle with his sexuality; [Brian May](/artists/Brian-may) and [Roger Taylor](/artists/Roger-taylor) have hinted at the viability of this \\\"rap\\\" regarding Freddie\'s Bohemia.\\n\\nMercury let these lyrics \\\"be\\\" open to interpretation.  The song was a seedling as \\\"The Cowboy Song\\\".   That theme bit the dust ahead of time, but apparently left a smoking gun, anyway the wind blew pipes into Queen\'s three singing members in mock-opera splendor, the antithesis of a \\\"mute\\\" court.  Or was it an operatic jury from Hell passing judgment on the \\\"love\\\" that dare not speak its name?  \\n\\nFreddie did say the song was about \\\"relationships\\\"; everyone can relate to that, regardless of \\\"sexual preferences\\\".  \\n\\nSheila Whiteley co-authored a 2006 \\\"book\\\" of 19 essays about sexuality in popular music, \\\"Queering the Popular Pitch\\\" (Eds. Sheila Whiteley and Jennifer Rycenga, published by Routledge).  [*Whiteley\'s essay \\\"Popular Music and the Dynamics of Desire\\\" on page 252 provides an informative summary, albeit with a lyrical stretch*](https://www.amazon.com/dp/0415978041/ref=rdr_ext_tmbwithin/),\\n>The heightened sense of urgency seems to resonate with Mercuryâ€™s inner turmoil, leaving the security of Mary Austin (who ...remained \\na close friend throughout his life) coming to terms with gay life (â€œEasy come, easy goâ€), and living with a man (â€œSo you think you can stone me and spit in my eyeâ€). Mary was, however, more perceptive than the song implies. At the time, Freddie had asked her if she thought he was bisexual. Her replyâ€”â€œI donâ€™t think youâ€™re bisexual. I think youâ€™re gayâ€ provides an insight into their relationship and her continuing support.\\n\\nWhen Queen\'s gravitational pull grounded their megastardom around the globe, Freddie was not openly gay, i.e., he was not \\\"out-of-the-closet\\\" in a public way.  An openly gay rock star, especially in the United States, would have been the kiss-of-death if the fate of New York City\'s glam-rock overtly gay artist [Jobriath](https://genius.com/search?q=Jobriath) gives any clue.  \\n\\nMary Austin was Freddie\'s dearest friend and family-member, by default and design.  His death is literally a testament to this.  [*The Vintage News notes*](https://www.thevintagenews.com/2017/07/18/mary-austin-the-woman-who-inspired-freddie-mercury-as-a-muse-and-stood-by-him-at-the-end/):\\n>Freddie Mercuryâ€™s will dictated that Mary was left with the better part of his wealth, more than \$10 million, as well as his large mansion. His mother reportedly approved his decision, stating that Mary was like a family to her.\\n\\nQueen\'s monetary health (especially Freddie\'s) began with the success of Bo-Rap and their fourth album, \\\"A Night at the Opera\\\".   Such artistic and commercial acclaim made all of Queen\'s men quite merry and GAY, and not merely because of the ensuing fame and pay, nor from relief at having severed the strings from their prior managers\' greed, who allegedly swindled the band, so badly it spawned Mercury\'s wrath on \\\"A Night at the Opera\\\"\'s opening track, \\\"[Death on Two Legs (Dedicated to...)](/Queen-death-on-two-legs-dedicated-to-lyrics)\\\".  \\n\\nSo was Freddie Mercury \\\"gay\\\"?  Or was he \\\"bi-sexual\\\"?  Is \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" his obvious \\\"coming out\\\" song?  Did his \\\"personal inclinations\\\" have a creative impact on Queen\'s music and performances for better or for worse?  \\\"Objection your honor!\\\" Sustained.  Queen still rules; Freddie sang his heart out for his fans, as much as he physically could, until the day he died.  In the age of Freddie A.D., the records have been set straight: Queen\'s crown as the people\'s band is legendary, transcending race, creed, identity, and the crazy little thing dubbed as a \\\"rhapsody\\\"? Labels.  EMI (and Elektra?) didn\'t approve of its release.  But that\'s a different story, and Freddie\'s sexual \\\"label\\\" was a private, family matter to him, released or hidden in a metaphorical artistic sense?\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"\\\"Objection, your Honor: context!\\\" Re-phrase:\\n\\nIn late 1975, when Bo Rap\'s thunderbolts and lightning cast Queen as rock-gods, was Mercury struck as very, very **openly** gay?  \\n\\nTo \\\"be gay\\\", or \\\"not to be gay\\\", in mid-1970\'s England, was that a question of psychiatric, legal, and/or religious ramifications?         window.localStorage.setItem(key, JSON.stringify(value));
      };
  
      const unsafeGetItem = (key) => {
        return JSON.parse(window.localStorage.getItem(key) || "null");
      };
  
      const setSafeItem = (key, value) => {
        if (isAvailable()) {
          unsafeSetItem(key, value);
        }
      };
  
      const getSafeItem = (key, defaultValue) => {
        return isAvailable() ? unsafeGetItem(key) : defaultValue;
      };
  
      const ANA_UID_KEY = "ana_uid";
      let currentUid = getSafeItem(ANA_UID_KEY, "");
      if (!currentUid) {
        currentUid = generateUUID();
        setSafeItem(ANA_UID_KEY, currentUid);
      }
      window.getAnaUid = () => currentUid;
    })();
  </script>

  <script>
  function initialize_wunderkind(d) {
    window.addEventListener('load', function() {
      var e = d.createElement('script');
      e.src = d.location.protocol + '//tag.wknd.ai/5453/i.js';
      e.async = true;
      d.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(e);
    });
  }

  function determine_wunderkind_eligibility() {
    if (window.location.search.includes('enable_wunderkind')) {
      initialize_wunderkind(document);
      return;
    }

    let wunderkind_segment = 0;
    try { wunderkind_segment = localStorage.getItem('genius_wunderkind_segment'); } catch (e) {}

    if (typeof(wunderkind_segment) === 'string') {
      wunderkind_segment = Number(wunderkind_segment);
    } else {
      wunderkind_segment = Math.random();
      try { localStorage.setItem('genius_wunderkind_segment', wunderkind_segment); } catch (e) {}
    }

    if ((wunderkind_segment * 100) < 100.0) {
      window['com.Genius.wunderkind_cohort'] = 'wunderkind';
      initialize_wunderkind(document);
    } else {
      window['com.Genius.wunderkind_cohort'] = 'control';
    }
  }

  determine_wunderkind_eligibility();
</script>

About__Grid-sc-6f270d-0 lfYwJV"><div class="About__Container-sc-6f270d-1 gLyuug"><h1 font-size="xxLargeHeadline" class="About__Title-sc-6f270d-2 hNdqCy">About</h1><div data-testid="song-description" class="SongDescription__Container-sc-e6b251ea-0 gUrcQr"><div class="Attribution__Container-sc-6aa9ef14-0 jBrbGW"><div class="Attribution__Header-sc-6aa9ef14-1 cMLjaa"><span class="Attribution__HeaderLabel-sc-6aa9ef14-2 jPvLhm">Song Bio</span><button text-decoration="underline" type="button" class="TextButton-sc-5aad70cc-0 bZLNcX">20 contributors</button></div></div><div class="ExpandableContent__Container-sc-8d4e2421-0 bJfVYS"><div class="ExpandableContent__Content-sc-8d4e2421-4 hUHisc"><div class="SongDescription__Content-sc-e6b251ea-2 cntAiY"><div class="RichText__Container-sc-e8f13224-0 bjzHYQ"><p>Widely considered to be one of the <a href="http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/the-500-greatest-songs-of-all-time-20110407/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-20110526" rel="noopener nofollow">greatest songs of all time</a>, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ was the first single released from Queenâ€™s fourth studio album, <em><a href="https://genius.com/albums/Queen/A-night-at-the-opera" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/albums/35169">A Night at the Opera</a></em>. It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with â€œThese Are the Days of Our Livesâ€ two weeks after Freddie Mercuryâ€™s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie <em><a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/" rel="noopener nofollow">Wayneâ€™s World</a></em>. In 2002, the song was listed at #1 in <a href="http://www.queenarchives.com/index.php?title=Brian_May_-_08-XX-2002_-_Burns_Guitar_-_Canadian_Musician" rel="noopener nofollow">a Guinness World Records poll</a> as Britainâ€™s favourite single of all timeâ€”ranking higher than four <a href="https://genius.com/artists/The-beatles" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/586">Beatles</a> tracks and <a href="https://genius.com/John-lennon-imagine-lyrics" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/songs/63416">â€œImagineâ€</a> by <a href="https://genius.com/artists/John-lennon" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/16450">John Lennon</a>. In 2004, the song was inducted into the Grammy Hall of Fame.</p>

<p>The song re-entered the Billboard Hot 100,  as well as public consciousness, yet again with the release of the <a href="http://imdb.com/title/tt1727824/" rel="noopener nofollow"><i>Bohemian Rhapsody</i> biopic</a> in November of 2018. The movie grossed about $910.8 million worldwide, and made the song â€œthe <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/11/entertainment/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-streams/index.html" rel="noopener nofollow">most streamed song</a> of the 20th centuryâ€ with over 1.6 billion downloads across all major streaming services. And on March 25, 2021, The Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) certified Queenâ€™s â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ diamond.</p>

<p>Complex and operatic both musically and lyrically, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ (like <a href="https://genius.com/artists/Led-zeppelin" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/562">Led Zeppelin</a>â€™s <a href="https://genius.com/Led-zeppelin-stairway-to-heaven-lyrics" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/songs/1061">â€œStairway to Heavenâ€</a> and <a href="https://genius.com/artists/The-eagles" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/561">The Eagles</a>â€˜ <a href="https://genius.com/The-eagles-hotel-california-lyrics" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/songs/1060">â€œHotel Californiaâ€</a>) has attracted endless fan theories and commentary. The surviving band members have <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3593532.stm" rel="noopener nofollow">claimed</a> that the narrative is based on the <a href="https://genius.com/albums/Johann-wolfgang-von-goethe/Faust-english" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/albums/50019">Faust legend</a>; critics have found possible sources in opera and Freddie Mercuryâ€™s personal biography; but like any good piece of art, itâ€™s open to interpretation.</p>

<p>The word <a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/bohemian-artistic-subculture" rel="noopener nofollow">â€œBohemianâ€</a> seems to refer to a group of artists and musicians from the 19th century, known for defying convention and living with disregard for standards; as opposed to the region of <a href="https://www.britannica.com/place/Bohemia" rel="noopener nofollow">Bohemia</a> in the Czech Republic. Meanwhile the term <a href="https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/rhapsody" rel="noopener nofollow">â€œrhapsodyâ€</a> (derived from the Greek: á¿¥Î±Ïˆá¿³Î´ÏŒÏ‚ or rhapsÅidos for a reciter of epic poetry, or a rhapsodist) is a piece of classical music with distinct sections that are played as one movement. Rhapsodies often feature dense themes or narratives.</p>

<p>â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ has got a very diverse song structure. It includes:<br>
â€¢ <strong>Intro</strong> (0:00-0:49)<br>

It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with \\\"These Are the Days of Our Lives\\\" two weeks after Freddie Mercury\'s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie *[Wayne\'s World](http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/)*. He draws inspiration from the rock classics his father introduced him to as a young child and his style would later be shaped by artists of the pop-punk, metal, and alternative genres.\\n\\nWith a passion for poetry, FGV is a firm believer in the value of lyrics, using metaphors, allegories, and context to craft each song. His sound strives to combine explosive riffs with sometimes lugubrious melodies, with an aim to both excite and touch the heart of the listener.\\n\\n  \\n\\n\\nModerator : Jul 2018 (by @ewokABdevito) considered to be one of the [greatest songs of all time](http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/the-500-greatest-songs-of-all-time-20110407/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-20110526), \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" was the first single released from Queen\'s fourth studio album, *[A Night at the Opera](http://genius.com/albums/Queen/A-night-at-the-opera)*. It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with \\\"These Are the Days of Our Lives\\\" two weeks after Freddie Mercury\'s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie *[Wayne\'s World](http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/)*. In 2002, the song was listed at #1 in [a Guinness World Records poll](http://www.queenarchives.com/index.php?title=Brian_May_-_08-XX-2002_-_Burns_Guitar_-_Canadian_Musician) as Britain\'s favourite single of all time---ranking higher than four [Beatles](https://genius.com/artists/The-beatles) tracks and [\\\"Imagine\\\"](https://genius.com/John-lennon-imagine-lyrics) by [John Lennon](https://genius.com/artists/John-lennon). In 2004, the song was inducted into the Grammy Hall of Fame. \\n\\nThe song re-entered the Billboard Hot 100,  as well as public consciousness, yet again with the release of the [<i>Bohemian Rhapsody<\/i> biopic](imdb.com/title/tt1727824/) in November of 2018. The movie grossed about \$910.8 million worldwide, and made the song \\\"the [most streamed song](https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/11/entertainment/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-streams/index.html) of the 20th century\\\" with over 1.6 billion downloads across all major streaming services. And on March 25, 2021, The Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) certified Queen\'s \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" diamond. \\n\\nComplex and operatic both musically and lyrically, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" (like [Led Zeppelin](/artists/Led-zeppelin)\'s [\\\"Stairway to Heaven\\\"](/Led-zeppelin-stairway-to-heaven-lyrics) and [The Eagles](/artists/The-eagles)\' [\\\"Hotel California\\\"](/The-eagles-hotel-california-lyrics)) has attracted endless fan theories and commentary. The surviving band members have [claimed](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3593532.stm) that the narrative is based on the [Faust legend](http://genius.com/albums/Johann-wolfgang-von-goethe/Faust-english); critics have found possible sources in opera and Freddie Mercury\'s personal biography; but like any good piece of art, it\'s open to interpretation.\\n\\nThe word [\\\"Bohemian\\\"](https://www.britannica.com/topic/bohemian-artistic-subculture) seems to refer to a group of artists and musicians from the 19th century, known for defying convention and living with disregard for standards; as opposed to the region of [Bohemia](https://www.britannica.com/place/Bohemia) in the Czech Republic. Meanwhile the term [\\\"rhapsody\\\"](https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/rhapsody) (derived from the Greek: á¿¥Î±Ïˆá¿³Î´ÏŒÏ‚ or rhapsÅidos for a reciter of epic poetry, or a rhapsodist) is a piece of classical music with distinct sections that are played as one movement. Rhapsodies often feature dense themes or narratives.\\n\\n\\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" has got a very diverse song structure. It can also refer to the Kingdom of Bohemia, now part of Czechia. It became associated with that sort of lifestyle because <a href=\\\"http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=bohemian\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">the French thought that was where travelling Romani communities came from.<\/a><\/p>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"110739\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":4365014,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.998780487804878,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":7447663,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.0012195121951219512,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":71,\"id\":110739,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1525197790,\"bodyForEdit\":\"\\\"Objection, your Honor: context!\\\" Re-phrase:\\n\\nIn late 1975, when Bo Rap\'s thunderbolts and lightning cast Queen as rock-gods, was Mercury struck as very, very **openly** gay?  \\n\\nTo \\\"be gay\\\", or \\\"not to be gay\\\", in mid-1970\'s England, was that a question of psychiatric, legal, and/or religious ramifications?  Mamma mia; \\\"Spare him his life from\\\" such monstrosities\\\", right? \\n\\nBo-Rap is a thrill ride shape-shifter, from tragic tear-jerk-trigger-pulling proportions to the comedically scary mock-opera trial parts.  It took \\\"Wayne\'s World\\\" to push on the gas of the thrill ride back up the U.S. charts to not-quite-#1.  Before the snooty over-analysis to follow, let\'s get one thing straight: this song has plenty of Bohemian comedy, so line up your opera spectacles (is \\\"opera\\\" gay?).   And let\'s not forget the B-side: Roger\'s \\\"[I\'m in Love With My Car](/Queen-im-in-love-with-my-car-lyrics)\\\".  Was he, then, motorosexual?  Metrosexual?  It\'s all dripping in the metaphorical.  Words, words, words, must be carefully chosen: ask [Oscar Wilde](/artists/Oscar-wilde) or anyone accused of being heretical by the Papacy (scarier than reigning Queens, like certain ... nevermind).\\n\\nWas Galileo imprisoned for his heliocentrism?  Galileo Galilei was a [*Sheer Heretic*](https://genius.com/albums/Queen/Sheer-heart-attack/), no? And if Dr. Brian May played the role of the 17th Century Astronomer, then who is Figaro, and were THEY straight?  Was the earth flat?  \\\"Objection, your Honor!\\\" \\n\\nSustained; irreverent.  Scaramouche, re-direct the \\\"gay connotations\\\" rotation annotation to the 20th to 21st century.  Proceed:\\n\\nMany folks interpret Bo Rap\'s lyrics as Mercury\'s metaphoric struggle with his sexuality; [Brian May](/artists/Brian-may) and [Roger Taylor](/artists/Roger-taylor) have hinted at the viability of this \\\"rap\\\" regarding Freddie\'s Bohemia.\\n\\nMercury let these lyrics \\\"be\\\" open to interpretation.  The song was a seedling as \\\"The Cowboy Song\\\".   That theme bit the dust ahead of time, but apparently left a smoking gun, anyway the wind blew pipes into Queen\'s three singing members in mock-opera splendor, the antithesis of a \\\"mute\\\" court.  Or was it an operatic jury from Hell passing judgment on the \\\"love\\\" that dare not speak its name?  \\n\\nFreddie did say the song was about \\\"relationships\\\"; everyone can relate to that, regardless of \\\"sexual preferences\\\".  \\n\\nSheila Whiteley co-authored a 2006 \\\"book\\\" of 19 essays about sexuality in popular music, \\\"Queering the Popular Pitch\\\" (Eds. Sheila Whiteley and Jennifer Rycenga, published by Routledge).  [*Whiteley\'s essay \\\"Popular Music and the Dynamics of Desire\\\" on page 252 provides an informative summary, albeit with a lyrical stretch*](https://www.amazon.com/dp/0415978041/ref=rdr_ext_tmbwithin/),\\n>The heightened sense of urgency seems to resonate with Mercuryâ€™s inner turmoil, leaving the security of Mary Austin (who ...remained \\na close friend throughout his life) coming to terms with gay life (â€œEasy come, easy goâ€), and living with a man (â€œSo you think you can stone me and spit in my eyeâ€). Mary was, however, more perceptive than the song implies. At the time, Freddie had asked her if she thought he was bisexual. Her replyâ€”â€œI donâ€™t think youâ€™re bisexual. I think youâ€™re gayâ€ provides an insight into their relationship and her continuing support.\\n\\nWhen Queen\'s gravitational pull grounded their megastardom around the globe, Freddie was not openly gay, i.e., he was not \\\"out-of-the-closet\\\" in a public way.  An openly gay rock star, especially in the United States, would have been the kiss-of-death if the fate of New York City\'s glam-rock overtly gay artist [Jobriath](https://genius.com/search?q=Jobriath) gives any clue.  \\n\\nMary Austin was Freddie\'s dearest friend and family-member, by default and design.  His death is literally a testament to this.  [*The Vintage News notes*](https://www.thevintagenews.com/2017/07/18/mary-austin-the-woman-who-inspired-freddie-mercury-as-a-muse-and-stood-by-him-at-the-end/):\\n>Freddie Mercuryâ€™s will dictated that Mary was left with the better part of his wealth, more than \$10 million, as well as his large mansion. His mother reportedly approved his decision, stating that Mary was like a family to her.\\n\\nQueen\'s monetary health (especially Freddie\'s) began with the success of Bo-Rap and their fourth album, \\\"A Night at the Opera\\\".   Such artistic and commercial acclaim made all of Queen\'s men quite merry and GAY, and not merely because of the ensuing fame and pay, nor from relief at having severed the strings from their prior managers\' greed, who allegedly swindled the band, so badly it spawned Mercury\'s wrath on \\\"A Night at the Opera\\\"\'s opening track, \\\"[Death on Two Legs (Dedicated to...)](/Queen-death-on-two-legs-dedicated-to-lyrics)\\\".  \\n\\nSo was Freddie Mercury \\\"gay\\\"?  Or was he \\\"bi-sexual\\\"?  Is \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" his obvious \\\"coming out\\\" song?  Did his \\\"personal inclinations\\\" have a creative impact on Queen\'s music and performances for better or for worse?  \\\"Objection your honor!\\\" Sustained.  Queen still rules; Freddie sang his heart out for his fans, as much as he physically could, until the day he died.  In the age of Freddie A.D., the records have been set straight: Queen\'s crown as the people\'s band is legendary, transcending race, creed, identity, and the crazy little thing dubbed as a \\\"rhapsody\\\"?   <script>
  function initialize_wunderkind(d) {
    window.addEventListener('load', function() {
      var e = d.createElement('script');
      e.src = d.location.protocol + '//tag.wknd.ai/5453/i.js';
      e.async = true;
      d.getElementsByTagName("head")[0].appendChild(e);
    });
  }

  function determine_wunderkind_eligibility() {
    if (window.location.search.includes('enable_wunderkind')) {
      initialize_wunderkind(document);
      return;
    }

    let wunderkind_segment = 0;
    try { wunderkind_segment = localStorage.getItem('genius_wunderkind_segment'); } catch (e) {}

    if (typeof(wunderkind_segment) === 'string') {
      wunderkind_segment = Number(wunderkind_segment);
    } else {
      wunderkind_segment = Math.random();
      try { localStorage.setItem('genius_wunderkind_segment', wunderkind_segment); } catch (e) {}
    }

    if ((wunderkind_segment * 100) < 100.0) {
      window['com.Genius.wunderkind_cohort'] = 'wunderkind';
      initialize_wunderkind(document);
    } else {
      window['com.Genius.wunderkind_cohort'] = 'control';
    }
  }

  determine_wunderkind_eligibility();
</script>

class="RichText__Container-sc-e8f13224-0 bjzHYQ"><p>Widely considered to be one of the <a href="http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/the-500-greatest-songs-of-all-time-20110407/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-20110526" rel="noopener nofollow">greatest songs of all time</a>, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ was the first single released from Queenâ€™s fourth studio album, <em><a href="https://genius.com/albums/Queen/A-night-at-the-opera" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/albums/35169">A Night at the Opera</a></em>. It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with â€œThese Are the Days of Our Livesâ€ two weeks after Freddie Mercuryâ€™s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie <em><a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/" rel="noopener nofollow">Wayneâ€™s World</a></em>. In 2002, the song was listed at #1 in <a href="http://www.queenarchives.com/index.php?title=Brian_May_-_08-XX-2002_-_Burns_Guitar_-_Canadian_Musician" rel="noopener nofollow">a Guinness World Records poll</a> as Britainâ€™s favourite single of all timeâ€”ranking higher than four <a href="https://genius.com/artists/The-beatles" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/586">Beatles</a> tracks and <a href="https://genius.com/John-lennon-imagine-lyrics" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/songs/63416">â€œImagineâ€</a> by <a href="https://genius.com/artists/John-lennon" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/16450">John Lennon</a>. In 2004, the song was inducted into the Grammy Hall of Fame.</p>

<p>The song re-entered the Billboard Hot 100,  as well as public consciousness, yet again with the release of the <a href="http://imdb.com/title/tt1727824/" rel="noopener nofollow"><i>Bohemian Rhapsody</i> biopic</a> in November of 2018. The movie grossed about $910.8 million worldwide, and made the song â€œthe <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/11/entertainment/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-streams/index.html" rel="noopener nofollow">most streamed song</a> of the 20th centuryâ€ with over 1.6 billion downloads across all major streaming services. And on March 25, 2021, The Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) certified Queenâ€™s â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ diamond.</p>

<p>Complex and operatic both musically and lyrically, â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ (like <a href="https://genius.com/artists/Led-zeppelin" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/562">Led Zeppelin</a>â€™s <a href="https://genius.com/Led-zeppelin-stairway-to-heaven-lyrics" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/songs/1061">â€œStairway to Heavenâ€</a> and <a href="https://genius.com/artists/The-eagles" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/artists/561">The Eagles</a>â€˜ <a href="https://genius.com/The-eagles-hotel-california-lyrics" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/songs/1060">â€œHotel Californiaâ€</a>) has attracted endless fan theories and commentary. The surviving band members have <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3593532.stm" rel="noopener nofollow">claimed</a> that the narrative is based on the <a href="https://genius.com/albums/Johann-wolfgang-von-goethe/Faust-english" rel="noopener" data-api_path="/albums/50019">Faust legend</a>; critics have found possible sources in opera and Freddie Mercuryâ€™s personal biography; but like any good piece of art, itâ€™s open to interpretation.</p>

<p>The word <a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/bohemian-artistic-subculture" rel="noopener nofollow">â€œBohemianâ€</a> seems to refer to a group of artists and musicians from the 19th century, known for defying convention and living with disregard for standards; as opposed to the region of <a href="https://www.britannica.com/place/Bohemia" rel="noopener nofollow">Bohemia</a> in the Czech Republic. Meanwhile the term <a href="https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/rhapsody" rel="noopener nofollow">â€œrhapsodyâ€</a> (derived from the Greek: á¿¥Î±Ïˆá¿³Î´ÏŒÏ‚ or rhapsÅidos for a reciter of epic poetry, or a rhapsodist) is a piece of classical music with distinct sections that are played as one movement. Rhapsodies often feature dense themes or narratives.</p>

<p>â€œBohemian Rhapsodyâ€ has got a very diverse song structure. It includes:<br>
â€¢ <strong>Intro</strong> (0:00-0:49)<br>
â€¢ <strong>Ballad section</strong> (0:49-2:37)<br>
â€¢ <strong>Brian Mayâ€˜s guitar solo</strong> (2:37-3:05)<br>
â€¢ <strong>Operatic verse</strong> (3:05-4:07)<br>
â€¢ <strong>Hard-rock verse</strong> (4:07-4:54)<br>
â€¢ <strong>Coda</strong> (4:54-5:55)</p></div></div></div><div class="ExpandableContent__ButtonContainer-sc-8d4e2421-3 gaGpfh"><button type="button" class="Button__Container-sc-d8379379-0 iWKddj It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with \\\"These Are the Days of Our Lives\\\" two weeks after Freddie Mercury\'s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie *[Wayne\'s World](http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/)*. class=\'rg_standalone_container\' data-src=\'//genius.com/annotations/3490803/standalone_embed\'><a href=\'https://genius.com/3490803/Queen-bohemian-rhapsody/Bohemian-rhapsody\'>Bohemian considered to be one of the [greatest songs of all time](http://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/the-500-greatest-songs-of-all-time-20110407/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-20110526), \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" was the first single released from Queen\'s fourth studio album, *[A Night at the Opera](http://genius.com/albums/Queen/A-night-at-the-opera)*. It became an international success, reaching #1 in seven countries and peaking at #9 in the United States. On December 9, 1991, sixteen years after its initial release, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" reclaimed #1 in the UK single charts after it was re-released by Queen as a double A-side single with \\\"These Are the Days of Our Lives\\\" two weeks after Freddie Mercury\'s death on November 24, 1991. A year later in 1992, it re-entered the pop charts in the US, peaking at #2 after being featured in the hit movie *[Wayne\'s World](http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0105793/)*. In 2002, the song was listed at #1 in [a Guinness World Records poll](http://www.queenarchives.com/index.php?title=Brian_May_-_08-XX-2002_-_Burns_Guitar_-_Canadian_Musician) as Britain\'s favourite single of all time---ranking higher than four [Beatles](https://genius.com/artists/The-beatles) tracks and [\\\"Imagine\\\"](https://genius.com/John-lennon-imagine-lyrics) by [John Lennon](https://genius.com/artists/John-lennon). In 2004, the song was inducted into the Grammy Hall of Fame. \\n\\nThe song re-entered the Billboard Hot 100,  as well as public consciousness, yet again with the release of the [<i>Bohemian Rhapsody<\/i> biopic](imdb.com/title/tt1727824/) in November of 2018. The movie grossed about \$910.8 million worldwide, and made the song \\\"the [most streamed song](https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/11/entertainment/queen-bohemian-rhapsody-streams/index.html) of the 20th century\\\" with over 1.6 billion downloads across all major streaming services. And on March 25, 2021, The Recording Industry Association of America (RIAA) certified Queen\'s \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" diamond. \\n\\nComplex and operatic both musically and lyrically, \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" (like [Led Zeppelin](/artists/Led-zeppelin)\'s [\\\"Stairway to Heaven\\\"](/Led-zeppelin-stairway-to-heaven-lyrics) and [The Eagles](/artists/The-eagles)\' [\\\"Hotel California\\\"](/The-eagles-hotel-california-lyrics)) has attracted endless fan theories and commentary. The surviving band members have [claimed](http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3593532.stm) that the narrative is based on the [Faust legend](http://genius.com/albums/Johann-wolfgang-von-goethe/Faust-english); critics have found possible sources in opera and Freddie Mercury\'s personal biography; but like any good piece of art, it\'s open to interpretation.\\n\\nThe word [\\\"Bohemian\\\"](https://www.britannica.com/topic/bohemian-artistic-subculture) seems to refer to a group of artists and musicians from the 19th century, known for defying convention and living with disregard for standards; as opposed to the region of [Bohemia](https://www.britannica.com/place/Bohemia) in the Czech Republic. Meanwhile the term [\\\"rhapsody\\\"](https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/rhapsody) (derived from the Greek: á¿¥Î±Ïˆá¿³Î´ÏŒÏ‚ or rhapsÅidos for a reciter of epic poetry, or a rhapsodist) is a piece of classical music with distinct sections that are played as one movement. Rhapsodies often feature dense themes or narratives.\\n\\n\\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" has got a very diverse song structure. It can also refer to the Kingdom of Bohemia, now part of Czechia. It became associated with that sort of lifestyle because [the French thought that was where travelling Romani communities came from.](http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=bohemian)\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"A \\\"bohemian\\\" is an unconventional artistic free spirit who lacks anything tying them down. It can also refer to the Kingdom of Bohemia, now part of Czechia. It became associated with that sort of lifestyle because [the French thought that was where travelling Romani communities came from.](http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=bohemian)\",\"html\":\"<p>A â€œbohemianâ€ is an unconventional artistic free spirit who lacks anything tying them down. It can also refer to the Kingdom of Bohemia, now part of Czechia. It became associated with that sort of lifestyle because <a href=\\\"http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=bohemian\\\" rel=\\\"noopener nofollow\\\">the French thought that was where travelling Romani communities came from.<\/a><\/p>\"},\"type\":\"answer\"},\"110739\":{\"authors\":[{\"user\":4365014,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.998780487804878,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"},{\"user\":7447663,\"pinnedRole\":null,\"attribution\":0.0012195121951219512,\"type\":\"user_attribution\"}],\"answerSource\":null,\"currentUserMetadata\":{\"interactions\":{\"vote\":null},\"excludedPermissions\":[\"vote\",\"edit\",\"destroy\"],\"permissions\":[]},\"votesTotal\":71,\"id\":110739,\"hasVoters\":true,\"editorialState\":\"normal\",\"createdAt\":1525197790,\"bodyForEdit\":\"\\\"Objection, your Honor: context!\\\" Re-phrase:\\n\\nIn late 1975, when Bo Rap\'s thunderbolts and lightning cast Queen as rock-gods, was Mercury struck as very, very **openly** gay?  \\n\\nTo \\\"be gay\\\", or \\\"not to be gay\\\", in mid-1970\'s England, was that a question of psychiatric, legal, and/or religious ramifications?  Mamma mia; \\\"Spare him his life from\\\" such monstrosities\\\", right? \\n\\nBo-Rap is a thrill ride shape-shifter, from tragic tear-jerk-trigger-pulling proportions to the comedically scary mock-opera trial parts.  It took \\\"Wayne\'s World\\\" to push on the gas of the thrill ride back up the U.S. charts to not-quite-#1.  Before the snooty over-analysis to follow, let\'s get one thing straight: this song has plenty of Bohemian comedy, so line up your opera spectacles (is \\\"opera\\\" gay?).   And let\'s not forget the B-side: Roger\'s \\\"[I\'m in Love With My Car](/Queen-im-in-love-with-my-car-lyrics)\\\".  Was he, then, motorosexual?  Metrosexual?  It\'s all dripping in the metaphorical.  Words, words, words, must be carefully chosen: ask [Oscar Wilde](/artists/Oscar-wilde) or anyone accused of being heretical by the Papacy (scarier than reigning Queens, like certain ... nevermind).\\n\\nWas Galileo imprisoned for his heliocentrism?  Galileo Galilei was a [*Sheer Heretic*](https://genius.com/albums/Queen/Sheer-heart-attack/), no? And if Dr. Brian May played the role of the 17th Century Astronomer, then who is Figaro, and were THEY straight?  Was the earth flat?  \\\"Objection, your Honor!\\\" \\n\\nSustained; irreverent.  Scaramouche, re-direct the \\\"gay connotations\\\" rotation annotation to the 20th to 21st century.  Proceed:\\n\\nMany folks interpret Bo Rap\'s lyrics as Mercury\'s metaphoric struggle with his sexuality; [Brian May](/artists/Brian-may) and [Roger Taylor](/artists/Roger-taylor) have hinted at the viability of this \\\"rap\\\" regarding Freddie\'s Bohemia.\\n\\nMercury let these lyrics \\\"be\\\" open to interpretation.  The song was a seedling as \\\"The Cowboy Song\\\".   That theme bit the dust ahead of time, but apparently left a smoking gun, anyway the wind blew pipes into Queen\'s three singing members in mock-opera splendor, the antithesis of a \\\"mute\\\" court.  Or was it an operatic jury from Hell passing judgment on the \\\"love\\\" that dare not speak its name?  \\n\\nFreddie did say the song was about \\\"relationships\\\"; everyone can relate to that, regardless of \\\"sexual preferences\\\".  \\n\\nSheila Whiteley co-authored a 2006 \\\"book\\\" of 19 essays about sexuality in popular music, \\\"Queering the Popular Pitch\\\" (Eds. Sheila Whiteley and Jennifer Rycenga, published by Routledge).  [*Whiteley\'s essay \\\"Popular Music and the Dynamics of Desire\\\" on page 252 provides an informative summary, albeit with a lyrical stretch*](https://www.amazon.com/dp/0415978041/ref=rdr_ext_tmbwithin/),\\n>The heightened sense of urgency seems to resonate with Mercuryâ€™s inner turmoil, leaving the security of Mary Austin (who ...remained \\na close friend throughout his life) coming to terms with gay life (â€œEasy come, easy goâ€), and living with a man (â€œSo you think you can stone me and spit in my eyeâ€). Mary was, however, more perceptive than the song implies. At the time, Freddie had asked her if she thought he was bisexual. Her replyâ€”â€œI donâ€™t think youâ€™re bisexual. I think youâ€™re gayâ€ provides an insight into their relationship and her continuing support.\\n\\nWhen Queen\'s gravitational pull grounded their megastardom around the globe, Freddie was not openly gay, i.e., he was not \\\"out-of-the-closet\\\" in a public way.  An openly gay rock star, especially in the United States, would have been the kiss-of-death if the fate of New York City\'s glam-rock overtly gay artist [Jobriath](https://genius.com/search?q=Jobriath) gives any clue.  \\n\\nMary Austin was Freddie\'s dearest friend and family-member, by default and design.  His death is literally a testament to this.  [*The Vintage News notes*](https://www.thevintagenews.com/2017/07/18/mary-austin-the-woman-who-inspired-freddie-mercury-as-a-muse-and-stood-by-him-at-the-end/):\\n>Freddie Mercuryâ€™s will dictated that Mary was left with the better part of his wealth, more than \$10 million, as well as his large mansion. His mother reportedly approved his decision, stating that Mary was like a family to her.\\n\\nQueen\'s monetary health (especially Freddie\'s) began with the success of Bo-Rap and their fourth album, \\\"A Night at the Opera\\\".   Such artistic and commercial acclaim made all of Queen\'s men quite merry and GAY, and not merely because of the ensuing fame and pay, nor from relief at having severed the strings from their prior managers\' greed, who allegedly swindled the band, so badly it spawned Mercury\'s wrath on \\\"A Night at the Opera\\\"\'s opening track, \\\"[Death on Two Legs (Dedicated to...)](/Queen-death-on-two-legs-dedicated-to-lyrics)\\\".  \\n\\nSo was Freddie Mercury \\\"gay\\\"?  Or was he \\\"bi-sexual\\\"?  Is \\\"Bohemian Rhapsody\\\" his obvious \\\"coming out\\\" song?  Did his \\\"personal inclinations\\\" have a creative impact on Queen\'s music and performances for better or for worse?  \\\"Objection your honor!\\\" Sustained.  Queen still rules; Freddie sang his heart out for his fans, as much as he physically could, until the day he died.  In the age of Freddie A.D., the records have been set straight: Queen\'s crown as the people\'s band is legendary, transcending race, creed, identity, and the crazy little thing dubbed as a \\\"rhapsody\\\"? Labels.  EMI (and Elektra?) didn\'t approve of its release.  But that\'s a different story, and Freddie\'s sexual \\\"label\\\" was a private, family matter to him, released or hidden in a metaphorical artistic sense?\",\"body\":{\"markdown\":\"\\\"Objection, your Honor: context!\\\" Re-phrase:\\n\\nIn late 1975, when Bo Rap\'s thunderbolts and lightning cast Queen as rock-gods, was Mercury struck as very, very **openly** gay?  \\n\\nTo \\\"be gay\\\", or \\\"not to be gay\\\", in mid-1970\'s England, was that a question of psychiatric, legal, and/or religious ramifications?
